# Forms: react-hook-form + zod + sonner

This is the reusable form pattern for every client site. See `AppointmentForm.tsx` for the
full reference.

## Schema first
- Define the schema in `src/lib/schemas/<name>.ts` with **zod**, then export the inferred type:
  `export type XValues = z.infer<typeof xSchema>`. Validation messages live in the schema.

## Wiring the form
- `const form = useForm<XValues>({ resolver: zodResolver(xSchema), defaultValues })`.
- Simple fields: spread `{...form.register("field")}` onto the shadcn `Input` / `Textarea`,
  with `aria-invalid={!!errors.field}`.
- Controlled shadcn components (e.g. `Select`): wrap in `<Controller control={form.control}
  name="field" render={({ field }) => <Select value={field.value} onValueChange={field.onChange}>…
  </Select>} />`.
- Show errors right under the field: `{errors.field && <p className="text-sm text-destructive">
  {errors.field.message}</p>}`. Pull `const { errors, isSubmitting } = form.formState`.

## Submit & feedback
- `<form onSubmit={form.handleSubmit(onSubmit)}>`. In `onSubmit(values)`: call the `@/lib/api`
  function, then on success `toast.success(...)`, `form.reset(defaults)`, and `onCreated?.()`;
  on failure `toast.error(err instanceof Error ? err.message : "…")`.
- Disable the submit `Button` with `disabled={isSubmitting}` and show a `Loader2Icon` spinner.
- **Feedback is via sonner toasts**, not inline success/error state. The `<Toaster />` is already
  mounted in `app/layout.tsx` — don't add another.
